{
  "stem": "1858.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 391.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, when we returned home, a horrible shock hit us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was then, on September 4th-- that was when the Nazis entered my home town.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was when we returned home that we felt the horrible impact of the war.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "For it was then that we found out that my only brother was shot.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we found out what happened.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "As they entered my hometown-- and my hometown, since being so close to the border, they actually entered through my street-- through our street.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as they entered, they immediately tried to terrorize the people, or frighten them, whatever.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They approached certain buildings, especially one building where my aunt lived, and hollered out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I found this out from my aunt, who survived that-- that they hollered out [GERMAN]-- all Jewish males come forward.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And from that building, 13 men came forth-- my uncle, my cousin, my brother, who was in my aunt's house, obviously, and my best girlfriend's father and two brothers-- all in all, 13 young men and-- men.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they were marched to the edge of town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were ordered to dig a ditch.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And of course, they obeyed, because first of all, that was the first day of the war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "No one knew what was planned for the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then having machine gun standing over you, you obey.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "When they finished, they were shot and buried in the mass grave.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I'm certain that in his death, my brother did not know why he was dying.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He was 15 years old.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He died only because he was a Jew, and for no other reason at all.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "You see, this was the very first day of the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
